Spitfire Squadron

War Documentary hosted by James Faulkner, published by History Channel broadcasted as part of HC Battle Stations series in 2000 - English narration 
http://docuwiki.net/images/a/a9/Spitfire-Squadron-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------

Designed in 1935 by Reginald Mitchell, the Supermarine Spitfire was a revolutionary fighter aircraft, which proved to be more than a match for its German opponents. In the summer of 1940, at a crucial moment in history, it helped turn the tide of World War Two, by providing Britain's vital air defence during the Battle of Britain. 
This is the inside story of the role of revolutionary fighter plane, with archive film, colour re-enactments and a first-hand account from Battle of Britain pilot Bob Doe.

Produced by Flashback Television for The History Channel

-- Extended interview of pilot Bob Doe joined to the file --
